### Create a new payment
POST http://localhost:8080/api/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 25.50,
  "currency": "USD",
  "webhook_url": "https://your-site.com/webhooks/payment",
  "success_url": "https://your-site.com/payment-success",
  "metadata": {
    "order_id": "12345",
    "customer_id": "user_789",
    "product": "Premium Subscription"
  }
}

### Get payment details
GET http://localhost:8080/api/payments/{{payment_id}}

### Get payment status
GET http://localhost:8080/api/payments/{{payment_id}}/status

### Access payment widget (redirect)
GET http://localhost:8080/widget/{{payment_id}}

### Health check
GET http://localhost:8080/health

### Example: Create test payment
POST http://localhost:8080/api/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 10.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "webhook_url": "https://webhook.site/unique-id",
  "success_url": "https://example.com/success",
  "metadata": {
    "test": true
  }
}

### Test Binance API directly (for debugging)
GET https://api.binance.com/api/v3/ticker/price?symbol=ETHUSDT

### Test Binance API - All prices
GET https://api.binance.com/api/v3/ticker/price

### Test Binance API - Multiple symbols
GET https://api.binance.com/api/v3/ticker/price?symbols=["ETHUSDT","SOLUSDT","TONUSDT"]

### Example: Real crypto amounts based on current prices
# First get current ETH price
GET https://api.binance.com/api/v3/ticker/price?symbol=ETHUSDT

# Then create payment to see conversion
POST http://localhost:8080/api/payments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 100.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "webhook_url": "https://webhook.site/test",
  "success_url": "https://example.com/success",
  "metadata": {
    "note": "Testing $100 payment with current Binance prices"
  }
}